CONFERENCE FEE
The TeleMed 94 conference fee includes Lunch on the first day, a Buffet
Reception/Dinner in the evening, Lunch on the second day and
refreshments during the conference breaks. Accommodation and Breakfast
are being provided at the nearby Kensington Hilton Hotel. Free transport
to and from the Hotel will be available on Thursday Evening and Friday
Morning.


WOLFSON CONFERENCE CENTRE
The Wolfson Conference Centre is located at the Hammersmith Hospital in
West London. It provides conference and meeting facilities for the Royal
Postgraduate Medical School which is a School of the University of
London. The School is an academic centre of excellence, internationally
renowned for its medical research, teaching and contributions to
clinical care.


EXHIBITION
There will be an associated exhibition by manufacturers and suppliers
who are supporting Telemedicine. This exhibition will be in the Wolfson
Conference Centre. Ample time is being provided in the programme to
allow all delegates to visit the exhibition.


HOTEL ACCOMMODATION AND REGISTRATION
Accommodation, included in the conference fee, is being provided at the
Kensington Hilton which is located in the same area of West London.
Early registration is strongly recommended as the organisers reserve the
right to accommodate delegates in other hotels if the allocation at the
Kensington Hilton is exceeded.

Delegates may register for the Kensington Hilton Hotel as they arrive at
the Conference Registration Desk at the Wolfson Conference Centre. There
will therefore be no need to go the Hotel before arriving at the
Conference.


